# === Experiment 10-8 Environment Variable Example: Copy to .env and fill in your Key ===

# Each player Agent uses Chat Completions (default current affordable flagship gpt-5.6-luna).
# First choice: OPENAI_API_KEY (direct connection to OpenAI); optional speech synthesis uses OpenAI TTS (tts-1) with the same Key.
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# Optional: override model (default gpt-5.6-luna)
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-5.6-luna

# General fallback: if OPENAI_API_KEY is not set, LLM decisions automatically switch to OPENROUTER_API_KEY via
# OpenRouter, and map the model name to its namespace (gpt-5.6-luna -> openai/gpt-5.6-luna).
# Tip: The gpt-5.6 series requires organization verification for direct OpenAI access; using OpenRouter is more convenient—
# just fill in OPENROUTER_API_KEY (leave OPENAI_API_KEY empty) to force routing through OpenRouter.
# Note: Speech synthesis (--voice, OpenAI tts-1) still only supports OPENAI_API_KEY; OpenRouter has no TTS endpoint.
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-your-openrouter-key
